description: Barker Minerals Ltd., an exploration stage company, acquires, explores for, and evaluates mineral properties in Canada. The company explores for gold, silver, platinum, palladium, copper, lead, zinc, diamond, molybdenum, and sulphide deposits. It has interests in the mineral claims located in the Goose Range area of the Cariboo mining district comprising approximately 51,451 hectares in east central British Columbia. The company was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Prince George, Canada.
